# MenuGen Project Overview

MenuGen is a Streamlit application that transforms restaurant menu images into actionable culinary content using advanced AI vision-language models.

## Core Applications

- **Primary**: [app_vlm.py](mdc:app_vlm.py) - Advanced VLM-based application with SmolVLM2
- **Legacy**: [app.py](mdc:app.py) - Original OCR-based version (maintained for reference)
- **Dependencies**: [requirements_vlm.txt](mdc:requirements_vlm.txt) - VLM app dependencies

## Key Features

1. **🔍 Vision-Language Understanding**: SmolVLM2 directly analyzes menu images (no OCR needed)
2. **🚀 Auto-Generation**: Automatically processes ALL detected dishes simultaneously  
3. **🥗 AI Ingredient Generation**: T5 model generates recipe ingredients for each dish
4. **🎨 AI Image Generation**: FLUX.1 creates professional food photography
5. **📊 Progress Tracking**: Real-time progress bars and status updates
6. **🎯 Organized Results**: Expandable sections with side-by-side content display

## Technology Stack

- **Frontend**: Streamlit with enhanced UX
- **Vision-Language**: SmolVLM2 (HuggingFaceTB/SmolVLM2-2.2B-Instruct)  
- **Recipe AI**: T5 Recipe Generation (flax-community/t5-recipe-generation)
- **Image Generation**: FLUX.1-schnell (black-forest-labs/FLUX.1-schnell)
- **Image Processing**: PIL, OpenCV
- **ML Framework**: PyTorch with GPU optimization

## Enhanced Workflow

1. User uploads menu image
2. **SmolVLM2 analyzes entire menu** (extracts all dishes intelligently)
3. **Automatic batch processing** of all detected dishes
4. **Parallel generation**: Ingredients + AI images for each dish
5. **Organized display**: Results in expandable sections with progress tracking
6. **Complete menu transformation**: From image to full culinary content